-- Philippine Equity Movers: Atlas Mining, Manila Electric
-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2012-04-12T02:16:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/atlas-gma-philippine-long-distance-philippine-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:12 a.m. in Manila.  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  rose 0.5 percent to
5,043.27.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development Corp. (AT)  
advanced 1.3 percent to 19.06 pesos, bound for the highest close
since Jan. 30. The metals producer’s Carmen Copper Corp. unit
shipped $32.8 million worth of copper, gold and magnetite in
March, a stock-exchange filing showed.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  , the nation’s largest
electricity retailer, gained 1.2 percent to 263 pesos, heading
for the highest close since March 20. The stock jumped as much
as 5.8 percent earlier today. The company said peak electricity
demand in the country’s main island of Luzon rose more than 300
megawatts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
